/**
 * mono_reverse: canonical note on the `rev_<Type>` helper pattern.
 *
 * This module intentionally defines no functions. It exists as a single place
 * for the note below, so greps for the shared convention land here instead of
 * in eight per-file copies.
 *
 * Owns:
 * - The rationale note below.
 *
 * Does not own:
 * - The type-specific reverse helpers themselves (`rev_strings`, `rev_i64s`,
 *   `rev_hir_expr`, `rev_mir_param`, `rev_lir_atom`, `reverse_tokens`, etc.).
 *   Those stay local to each module because they reference IR types that must
 *   not leak into common/ — consolidating them would create a central
 *   god-module importing from every IR/frontend/backend file.
 *
 * Monomorphic reverse helpers (list.reverse has codegen issues in nxc):
 * the generic `stdlib/list.reverse` call emits invalid WASM under the current
 * self-hosted codegen (verified 2026-04-23: "type mismatch: expected i64 but
 * nothing on stack" when running the emitted binary). Every hot path therefore
 * uses a type-specialized tail-recursive `rev_<Type>` helper instead. When the
 * codegen bug is fixed, these per-file workarounds can all drop in favor of
 * `list.reverse` and this module can be deleted.
 */
